The paper deals with designing optimal adversarial noise algorithms for settings where a learner has access to multiple classifiers. This involves the use of game theory and optimization techniques to compute Nash equilibrium and design best response oracles. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with security and privacy concerns related to adversarial attacks, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
